  "prompt": "What are some good probiotic foods I should add to my diet?",
  "response": "Here are some excellent probiotic foods to consider adding to your diet:\n\n1. Yogurt\n- Contains live active cultures\n- Look for \"live and active cultures\" on the label\n- Greek yogurt is a good option\n\n2. Kefir\n- Fermented milk drink\n- Contains multiple strains of probiotics\n- Can be dairy or water-based\n\n3. Sauerkraut\n- Fermented cabbage\n- Rich in probiotics and nutrients\n- Choose unpasteurized varieties\n\n4. Kimchi\n- Korean fermented vegetables\n- Spicy and probiotic-rich\n- Made with cabbage and other vegetables\n\n5. Kombucha\n- Fermented tea\n- Contains beneficial bacteria\n- Available in many flavors\n\n6. Miso\n- Japanese fermented soybean paste\n- Used in soups and marinades\n- Contains beneficial bacteria\n\n7. Tempeh\n- Fermented soybean product\n- High in protein and probiotics\n- Can be used as a meat substitute\n\n8. Pickles (fermented in salt water)\n- Contain live cultures\n- Choose naturally fermented varieties\n\nRemember to introduce these foods gradually and choose varieties with live active cultures.",
